## 7. Functional Requirements

### 7.1 Pre-Validation System Checks (Post S2, Pre BL-check)

After the user submits R-Number + Port, the system must check and handle 6 error conditions in sequence before proceeding to BL validation:

| Error | Trigger | Required UI Behaviour |
|---|---|---|
| E1 — ASYCUDA down | System unreachable | Hard stop. Show retry option. No user action beyond retry. |
| E2 — R-No not found | ASYCUDA returns null | Hard stop. Prompt user to verify R-Number. |
| E3 — Form not assessed | Form exists but not processed | Wait state. Show "not yet assessed" message. Show refresh. |
| E4 — Form locked | Another officer has form open | Wait state. Show "form is locked" message. Show refresh. |
| E5 — Insufficient funds | Payment account balance too low | Block. Direct user to top up account. |
| E6 — Account mismatch | FF account incompatible with consignee code | Block. Direct user to contact customs finance. |

### 7.2 BL Validation

If all 6 pre-checks pass:
1. Extract BL Number from ASYCUDA form data
2. Send BL to Tradian — if not found → E1/S5 (BL not found screen)
3. Send BL to E-Customs — if not registered → E2/S6 (technical error screen)
4. Send BL + 7 fields to E-Valuator for cross-check
5. If all 7 fields match → Write-off success screen
6. If any field fails → S4 field mismatch screen

### 7.3 The 7 Validated Fields

| Field | MCS-117 Fine Tier |
|---|---|
| Gross Weight | Tier II — MVR 1,000 |
| Package Code | Tier II — MVR 1,000 |
| Packs Number | Tier II — MVR 1,000 |
| Exporter | Tier I — MVR 500 |
| Consignee | Tier II — MVR 1,000 |
| Carrier | Tier I — MVR 500 |
| BL Number | Tier II — MVR 1,000 |

### 7.4 BL Not Found — Cancel Request (E1/S5)

When BL is not found in Tradian:
- Inform user the BL has not been received by customs
- Direct user to contact Tradian
- Provide BL Cancel Request submission:
  - Upload: Supporting letter (PDF/image)
  - Upload: The BL document itself (PDF)
  - Submit → goes to admin review queue (same S8 flow as amendment)

### 7.5 Amendment Form — Digital MCS-117 (S7)

Triggered by: S4 field mismatch OR E4 late manifest

Form must capture:
- Manifest details (pre-filled from ASYCUDA data)
- Service type selection (House BL amendment / Master BL amendment / Late manifest)
- Amendment type selection with fine tier displayed per field
- Content before/after change (pre-fill "before" from ASYCUDA, user fills "after")
- Reason for amendment (free text)
- Supporting documents upload:
  - Original amended manifest with company stamp
  - Original BL/AWB after content change
  - No-objection letter from Exporter (if consignee change)
  - No-objection letter from Shipper (if "to order" consignment)
- Declaration checkbox
- Signature fields: Shipping Agent + Consignee (original + new if applicable)

### 7.6 Fine Calculation

System must auto-calculate fine based on which fields are being amended:
- Late manifest submission: MVR 3,000 (fixed)
- Tier I fields amended: MVR 500 per application (not per field)
- Tier II fields amended: MVR 1,000 per application (not per field)
- If both tiers amended: MVR 1,000 (higher tier applies)
- Total charged to FF account code (e.g. FF00056)

### 7.7 Admin Review (S8)

After amendment or BL cancel submission:
- Application enters review queue for Customs Officer
- Officer can: Approve or Reject
- On Reject: Applicant notified with reason, can re-submit to S7
- On Approve: Payment gateway triggered

### 7.8 Payment

- Fine charged to FF (Freight Forwarder) unique account code
- System must validate FF account before triggering payment
- Payment methods: Bank transfer (BML/MIB), BML Internet Banking, Cash at counter
- On payment confirmation: write-off finalized using amended data

