## 8. Non-Functional Requirements

| Category | Requirement |
|---|---|
| Availability | 99.5% uptime during business hours (07:30–16:00 MVT) |
| Response time | S2 validation < 15 seconds end-to-end across all 4 APIs |
| Security | API keys stored in environment variables, never exposed to frontend |
| Auth | Supabase Auth — magic link + username/password |
| Audit | Every state transition logged with timestamp, user ID, IP |
| Language | English primary, Dhivehi labels where required |
| Browser support | Chrome, Firefox, Safari — latest 2 versions |
| Responsive | Desktop and tablet (1024px+). Mobile read-only status view |

---

## 9. Assumptions & Dependencies

- ASYCUDA, E-Valuator, E-Customs, and Tradian all expose REST APIs with stable endpoints
- Each external system provides an API key for authentication
- The FF account code is retrievable from the ASYCUDA form or known to the user
- Admin review is handled via a separate officer portal (out of scope v1.0)
- Email notifications are sent via Supabase Edge Functions

